   "source": [
    "# 🔍 Assertions in Python\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣ What is an Assertion?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Definition\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "An **Assertion** is a statement used to check whether a condition is **True** or **False** during program execution.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "If the condition is:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ **True** → Program continues normally.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "❌ **False** → Program stops and raises an **AssertionError**.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Simple Meaning\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "**Assertion = Checking a condition**\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Think of it as a safety check in your program.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert condition\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "If the condition is correct, nothing happens.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "If the condition is wrong, Python raises an error.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 2️⃣ Real-World Analogy\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## 🏧 ATM Machine Example\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Before allowing a transaction, the ATM checks:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "Is the PIN correct?\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Case 1: Correct PIN\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "PIN Correct\r\n",
    "      ↓\r\n",
    "Proceed Transaction\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Case 2: Wrong PIN\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "PIN Wrong\r\n",
    "      ↓\r\n",
    "Stop Transaction\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "This checking process is similar to an **Assertion**.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 3️⃣ Syntax of Assertion\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Basic Syntax\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert condition\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Flow\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "Condition True  → Continue Program\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Condition False → AssertionError\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 4️⃣ Simple Assertion Example\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "x = 10\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert x > 5\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "print(\"Valid\")\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "Valid\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Explanation\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "10 > 5\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Condition is True, so the program continues.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 5️⃣ When Assertion Fails\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "x = 2\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert x > 5\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "print(\"Valid\")\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "AssertionError\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Explanation\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "2 > 5\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Condition is False.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Python immediately stops the program.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 6️⃣ Assertion with Custom Message\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Instead of showing only:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "AssertionError\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "we can display our own message.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Syntax\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert condition, \"Error Message\"\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Example\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "age = 15\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert age >= 18, \"Age must be 18+\"\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "print(\"Allowed\")\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "AssertionError: Age must be 18+\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Real-World Analogy\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "🎬 Cinema Ticket\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Condition:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "Age >= 18\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "If not:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "Not Allowed\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "The custom message tells the user why the assertion failed.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 7️⃣ Why Do We Use Assertions?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Assertions help programmers find mistakes early.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Benefits\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Debugging\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Checking assumptions\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Finding bugs quickly\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Verifying expected values\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Testing program logic\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 8️⃣ How Assertions Work\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "Program Starts\r\n",
    "      ↓\r\n",
    "Check Condition\r\n",
    "      ↓\r\n",
    "Condition True?\r\n",
    "      ↓\r\n",
    "   Yes      No\r\n",
    "    ↓        ↓\r\n",
    "Continue   AssertionError\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 9️⃣ Assertion Examples\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Example 1: Positive Number Check\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "num = 10\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert num > 0\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "print(\"Positive Number\")\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "Positive Number\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Example 2: Marks Validation\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "marks = 95\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert marks <= 100, \"Marks cannot exceed 100\"\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "print(\"Valid Marks\")\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "Valid Marks\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Example 3: Division Check\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "denominator = 5\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert denominator != 0, \"Cannot divide by zero\"\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "result = 10 / denominator\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "print(result)\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "2.0\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 🔟 Types of Assertion Usage\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "There are mainly two ways to use assertions.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## 1. Simple Assertion\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "x = 10\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert x > 0\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "No custom message.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## 2. Assertion with Message\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "x = -5\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert x > 0, \"Number must be positive\"\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Provides a meaningful error message.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣1️⃣ AssertionError\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "When an assertion fails, Python raises:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "AssertionError\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Example:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert False\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "AssertionError\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## AssertionError with Message\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert False, \"Something went wrong\"\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "AssertionError: Something went wrong\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣2️⃣ Assertions vs Exceptions\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "| Feature        | Assertion            | Exception               |\r\n",
    "| -------------- | -------------------- | ----------------------- |\r\n",
    "| Purpose        | Debugging            | Error Handling          |\r\n",
    "| Keyword        | assert               | try-except              |\r\n",
    "| Raises         | AssertionError       | Various Exceptions      |\r\n",
    "| Used For       | Checking assumptions | Handling runtime errors |\r\n",
    "| Production Use | Limited              | Common                  |\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Assertion Example\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "x = 10\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert x > 0\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Exception Example\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "try:\r\n",
    "    num = 10 / 0\r\n",
    "except ZeroDivisionError:\r\n",
    "    print(\"Cannot divide by zero\")\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣3️⃣ Where Are Assertions Used?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## A. Debugging\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Check whether variables contain expected values.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "total = 100\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert total >= 0\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## B. Testing\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Verify that output is correct.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "result = 5 + 5\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert result == 10\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## C. Data Validation During Development\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "salary = 50000\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert salary > 0\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## D. Function Preconditions\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "def square_root(num):\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "    assert num >= 0, \"Number cannot be negative\"\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "    return num ** 0.5\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "print(square_root(25))\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "5.0\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣4️⃣ Important Warning\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Many beginners use assertions for user input validation.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Example:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "age = int(input(\"Enter Age: \"))\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert age >= 18\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "⚠️ This is NOT recommended.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Why?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Because assertions can be disabled.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "For user inputs, use:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "if\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "or\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "try-except\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "instead.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣5️⃣ Assertions Can Be Disabled\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Python can ignore assertions using optimization mode.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Command\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```bash\r\n",
    "python -O file.py\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Example\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert False\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "print(\"Program Running\")\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Normally:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "AssertionError\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "With:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```bash\r\n",
    "python -O file.py\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Output:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "Program Running\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "The assertion is skipped.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣6️⃣ Common Mistakes\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## ❌ Using Assertions for User Input\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "age = int(input())\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "assert age >= 18\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Not recommended.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## ❌ Forgetting Error Messages\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert marks > 0\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Better:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert marks > 0, \"Marks must be positive\"\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## ❌ Using Assertions for Security Checks\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert password == \"admin\"\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Bad practice because assertions can be disabled.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣7️⃣ Best Practices\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Use assertions for debugging.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Use meaningful messages.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Use assertions to check assumptions.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Use assertions in testing.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "❌ Don't use assertions for user validation.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "❌ Don't use assertions for security checks.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣8️⃣ Real-Time Use Cases\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Software Development\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Check internal program logic.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Testing\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Verify expected outputs.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert add(2, 3) == 5\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Data Science\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Check data quality.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert len(data) > 0\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "## Machine Learning\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Verify input dimensions.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert rows == columns\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 1️⃣9️⃣ Complete Example\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "def withdraw(balance, amount):\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "    assert amount > 0, \"Amount must be positive\"\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "    assert amount <= balance, \"Insufficient Balance\"\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "    balance -= amount\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "    return balance\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "print(withdraw(1000, 500))\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Output\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```text\r\n",
    "500\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 2️⃣0️⃣ Interview Questions\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Q1. What is an Assertion?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "An assertion is a statement used to check whether a condition is True during program execution.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Q2. Which keyword is used for assertions?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Q3. Which error is raised when an assertion fails?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "AssertionError\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Q4. Can assertions have custom messages?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Yes\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "assert condition, \"Message\"\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Q5. Can assertions be disabled?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Yes\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```bash\r\n",
    "python -O file.py\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Q6. Are assertions used for debugging?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "✅ Yes\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "### Q7. Should assertions be used for user input validation?\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "❌ No\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Use:\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "if\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "or\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "```python\r\n",
    "try-except\r\n",
    "```\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "instead.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 🎯 2-Minute Classroom Explanation\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "\"An assertion is a statement used to check whether a condition is true or false during program execution. We use the `assert` keyword in Python. If the condition is true, the program continues normally. If the condition is false, Python raises an `AssertionError` and stops execution. Assertions are mainly used for debugging, testing, and checking assumptions in code. We can also provide custom error messages using `assert condition, message`. Assertions should not be used for user input validation because they can be disabled using Python's optimization mode.\"\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "---\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "# 🚀 Final One-Line Summary\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "**Assertion is a debugging tool that checks whether a condition is true and raises an `AssertionError` if the condition is false.**\r\n"
   ]
